Jenkins Pipeline Visualization and Logs 
Tasks: View pipeline stages, analyze logs, debug failures. 
Outcome: CI troubleshooting skills. 

Aim 
To analyse Jenkins pipeline execution using Stage View and console logs in order to understand 
pipeline visualization and CI troubleshooting. 
Theory 
Jenkins provides Pipeline Visualization to graphically represent stage execution, duration, and 
status. 
The Stage View helps identify failed stages, execution time, and build trends, while console 
logs assist in debugging failures. 
This improves observability and troubleshooting in CI pipelines. 

Procedure / Steps 
Steps 1–6 are the same as Experiment 9. 

Step 7: Open Pipeline Stage View 
• Open Stage View of a built pipeline job 
• Displays graphical representation of pipeline stages. 

Step 8: Analyse Stage Execution 
• Observe stages: Build, Test, Deploy 
• Check: Execution time, Success / failure status 
• Helps identify performance and failure points. 

Step 9: Identify Failed Builds 
• Red-coloured stages → failed build numbers (add line > bat 'exit')

Step 10: Analyze Console Logs 
• Provides detailed logs for error analysis. 

Step 11: Compare Successful vs Failed Runs 
• Compare timings and logs across builds 
• Helps understand stability and pipeline behaviour.
